Winelands
Slaves were the backbone of the colonial economy.
They outnumbered Europeans, yet it is all but forgotten who built and maintained public buildings and roads in the colony, who did the back-breaking work in the vineyards and orchards of Boland farms, who helped to build the imposing homesteads and who made furniture, vats, wagons, clothes and other forms of cultural material that we still see around us today.
Slave sales were held on farms and auctions took place in Stellenbosch.
Slaves were punished and executed in Stellenbosch in public, as well as in the Old Goal.
Arson, one of the most frequent transgressions, was punishable by hanging.
