The Bokkeveld slave rebels (see Ceres for more information) were put on trial here in 1826.
Their leaders, Galant and Abel, were sentenced to death.
Rhenish Mission Church (46 Adderley Street) The headquarters of the Rhenish Mission Society in South Africa moved from Steinthal, Tulbagh, to Worcester.
A beautiful church and parsonage were built in 1852 to replace the Gesticht of the Dutch Reformed Church that was used since 1832.
Rhenish School (corner of Adderley and High streets) Missionary Ter Linden started the first school for slave children here on 18 January 1834.
Today this site is part of a cafÉ.
