How will compensation from the RAF affect a Social Security grant?
If, taking into account any compensation you get from the Road Accident Fund, your income is still below the means test set by SASSA, you may qualify for one of the Social Security grants.
In other words, if your income (including the compensation from the RAF) is less than R1410 per month, you may qualify also for the disability grant.
