There is hereby established an agency for the promotion of trade and investment in the Province to be known as Trade and Investment KwaZulu-Natal.
The Agency is a juristic person.
The Agency is a provincial public entity subject to the Public Finance Management Act, 1999 .
The objects of the Agency are ―
to attract foreign and domestic investment;
to generate exports and export capacity; and
to perform the powers, duties and functions specified in section 4.
The Agency must ―
identify, develop, market and promote investment opportunities in the Province to international and domestic investors;
develop the export capacity of the Province;
develop the export market of the Province;
foster trade and investment within the Province;
develop a provincial investment and export plan for the development, promotion and marketing of investment in and exports from the Province; and
keep and maintain a database of investment opportunities within the Province in such a manner as to benefit all sectors of the economy.
The Agency may ―
for the purposes of developing, promoting, and marketing investment in and the export capacity of the Province, and subject to the prior written approval of the responsible Member of the Executive Council ―
establish and operate one or more companies, close corporations or other similar bodies, and to buy and sell shares in such companies, close corporations or other such similar bodies;
enter into joint ventures with other institutions, organisations, municipalities, bodies or persons;
become partners or shareholders in companies, close corporations or other bodies and to sell all or part of such shares or interests; and
raise funds through donations and sponsorships;
liaise with any other entity, organ of state, organisation or institution whose activities or aims have an impact on and relate to the development, promotion or marketing of investment in the Province;
investigate and make recommendations to the Executive Council, through the responsible Member of the Executive Council on any matter relating directly or indirectly to the promotion, development or marketing of investment in the Province;
enter into agreements for the attainment of its objects, the exercise of its powers, duties and functions or the management and administration of its affairs, whether or not expressly provided for in this section; and
do any other thing or attend to any other matter that the responsible Member of the Executive Council considers necessary for the proper implementation of this Act.
In addition to the powers referred to in subsection, the Agency, has the powers referred to in section 34 of, and Schedule 2 to, the Companies Act, 1973 .
The Board consists of ―
at least five, but not more than 20, members appointed by the responsible Member of the Executive Council; and
the Chief Executive Officer, ex officio, as contemplated in section 17.
Members of the Board must be fit and proper persons to serve the best interests of the Province, collectively possessing ―
appropriate knowledge or experience in organised constituencies within the business industry; and
the following skills and expertise ―
legal skills, experience and qualifications;
financial skills, experience and qualifications;
investment and export experience or qualifications;
labour market experience or qualifications;
human resource or educational experience or qualifications;
community development skills and experience; and
planning or development skills and experience.
In appointing members to the Board, the responsible Member of the Executive Council must ensure that ―
historic imbalances are addressed;
the Board, collectively possess the necessary and appropriate skills and expertise;
the Board is representative of persons employed or involved in the import, export, trade and investment business enterprises in the Province;
municipal interests are represented on the Board in such a manner that equitable spatial representation of municipalities is achieved: Provided that no more than four persons may be appointed to the Board to give effect to the provisions of this paragraph; and
organised local government is represented on the Board.
The responsible Member of the Executive Council-
must designate
one of the members of the Board as the Chairperson of the Board; and
one of the members of the Board as the Deputy Chairperson of the Board.
the nomination procedure;
the requirements for nomination; and
the closing date for the nomination.
