﻿The Portfolio Committee must consult the public about the Bill . 
A Deputy Speaker , also elected from amongst the Members of the Legislature assists the Speaker . 
Committee meetings are open to the public and the most important change is that everyone has the right to attend all meetings of the Portfolio Committees . 
Everything they say or do must be open so that you , the voters , can know what decisions are being made . 
If they want to make a law , they must ask the Legislature to do it . 
The Constitution says that there must be public access and involvement in all tiers of government . 
The party that has won the majority of votes is the party that will have the majority of Members in the Legislature . 
The NCOP forms part of the national legislative process where the provinces can vote as province on matters effecting provinces and as representatives of their respective political parties on matters of national interest . 
The party with the majority of votes will form the government that will rule the country for the next term of five years . 
Every year the Legislature will approve the budget of the province , which sets out the finances that the Premier and each MEC needs to spend during that year in effectively running the various departments . 
He/she is elected by the members of the Legislature . 
It is here that the Bill is discussed and changes can be made here . 
The delegates representing each delegation are from the Provincial Legislature , and reflect the strength of the different parties in the province . 
Every voice is important . 
The Presiding Officer in the Legislature is known as the Speaker of the Legislature . 
One of the rules outlined in the Constitution says that there must be public access and involvement in Parliament and the Legislature . 
You can get the addresses and telephone numbers of these Constituency offices by phoning the legislature or one of the political parties . 
Acting in accordance with the Constitution , each of the nine provinces has its own legislature consisting of between 30 and 80 members , depending on the size of the population . 
After the elections , each of the Provincial Legislatures elects a new Premier . 
The political head of the NCOP is the Chairperson , and one permanent Deputy Chairperson as well as one rotating Deputy Chairperson supports him/her . 
