in the case of a private body ; the requester must state the right that is to be exercised or protected and why the record requested is required for the exercise or protection of such right .
note : requesters who cannot read or write can make oral requests to the information officer of a public body who must fill in the request form for the requester .
who can make a request for access to a record ?
a requester may make a request for access to records of a private or public body .
the requesters right of access to a record of a private or public body includes a right of access to a record containing personal information about the requester , or a person on whose behalf the request is made .
a public body may make a request for access to a record of a private body for the exercise or protection of any rights other than its rights , only if it is acting in the public interest .
