the information officer of a public body must refuse a request for access to a record of that body , if its disclosure could reasonably be expected to endanger the life or physical safety of an individual .
the information officer of a public body may refuse a request for access to a record of that body , if its disclosure would likely prejudice or impair :
the security of a building , structure , or system , including a computer or communication system , a means of transport or any other property ;
the information officer of a public body may refuse a request for access to a record of that body , if its disclosure would likely prejudice or impair the methods , systems , plans or procedure for the protection of :
an individual under a witness protection scheme ;
