how did the city decide upon phase 1a ?
as a host city for the 2010 soccer world cup , the city of cape town has signed a contract with fifa to provide transport services between the airport , the city centre and the green point stadium area .
phase 1a also focuses upon delivering quality public transport to the west coast which includes some of the communities with the most pressing mobility needs , such as mamre , atlantis , doornbach , du noon , and the joe slovo informal settlement , near milnerton .
this west coast area also currently experiences some of the most severe traffic congestion .
on 27 august 2008 the city of cape town gave the go-ahead for phase 1a , and approved the budget of r1.3 billion .
