what to do if your child disappears
report the case at your nearest saps station or dial 10111 .
you dont have to wait 24 hours !
what parents can do :
videotape and photograph your child two to three times per year .
do not leave your child unattended while shopping , visiting with neighbours or friends , or running errands .
under no circumstances should you leave your child alone in a car .
make sure your child always checks with you before going anywhere with anyone .
make sure your child learns his or her address and phone number at an early age .
a second phone number of a friend or relative is also helpful .
teach your child how to make an emergency call and to begin with im in trouble ; i need your help
make sure your child knows to scream and run if approached in a frightening way by anyone .
your child should be taught to always tell you immediately if he or she is approached by a stranger who asks for help , offers gifts or sweets , or frightens him or her in any way .
plan the safest route to your destination .
choose busy , well-lit streets .
walk facing oncoming traffic so you can see and be seen .
walk near curbs to avoid being surprised by someone who may be hiding in bushes or shrubbery .
stay out of reach if someone in a vehicle asks directions .
do not play in deserted areas such as empty playgrounds , parks , construction sites or dumps .
use the buddy-system ― play , walk , bike or skate with a friend .
always let your parents know when you arrive home safely .
never go near strange vehicles !
scream , kick and yell !
